messages.messageBody:
Thanks so much for this link, we're enjoying checking in with the birds... I
must share a family funny :) For the two years Hayden had his daddy, he
never saw him with hair. When we went to the zoo and I said, "there's a bald
eagle" He said, "just like daddy!" so every bald eagle we've ever seen since
then has been named Mitch <bwg>

diana,
The wackiest widow westriver...

----- Original Message -----
From: Mary
To: Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, April 29, 2003 6:02 PM
Subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] Re: Eagles


From: <HOMESCHOOL4GOOD@...>

<< Northeast Utilities is in Hartford, CT and a pair of eagles are nesting
there; this is their online camera! >>
Thanks for passing this on, it's so cool!
Kim>>



The Kodak building in NY has a camera on a nest box they put up years ago.
They have it every year and always show the two peregrine falcons come back
to mate. You get to see the eggs from day one and them watch the babies fly
away. For the past 2 years though it's been a new male with the same female
as before. They don't know what happened to her usual mate.

Mary B
